apps.description:
This is my OS written in Java. When you open it, the easiest way to close it is to use the Shut Down button found by clicking on the menu in the bottom right hand corner. This OS was written to run Java applications inside of it. The only application that I have included with this version of NathaNOS is my clock application. To run a java program inside of it, drag and drop the jar file into the NathaNOS1.1/assets and you should be ready to go!</p> <p>Note: if you want to add one of your own java programs to NathaNOS, then you will have to make the main class extend a JFrame, and you will have to make the constructor of your main class have one parameter that is a Boolean for visibility. You can see an example below:<br><pre><code>package clock;

import javax.swing.JFrame;

public class Main extends JFrame
{
public Main(Boolean visibility)	{
		this.setVisible(visibility.booleanValue());
	}
}
</code></pre>
